events.name: Lithium Market and Production Adjustments
events.wd_description: The lithium market is entering a bottoming out phase with production adjustments across various regions, impacting overall supply and pricing dynamics.
events.description: The lithium market is entering a bottoming out phase with production adjustments across various regions, impacting overall supply and pricing dynamics.

events.name: Cost Support for Prices
events.wd_description: Current lithium salt prices are nearing the cost line for some mines, which may provide price support as the market enters a bottoming out phase.
events.description: Current lithium salt prices are nearing the cost line for some mines, which may provide price support as the market enters a bottoming out phase.

events.name: Cost Analysis
events.wd_description: Analysis of production costs indicates that lithium prices are close to the break-even point for several mines.

events.name: Price Support Mechanisms
events.wd_description: Cost pressures may provide support for lithium prices, preventing further declines as the market stabilizes.

events.name: Production Adjustments in Australia
events.wd_description: Several Australian lithium mines are adjusting their production schedules, with some projects facing temporary shutdowns and others progressing with expansion plans.
events.description: Several Australian lithium mines are adjusting their production schedules, with some projects facing temporary shutdowns and others progressing with expansion plans.

events.name: Finniss Mine
events.wd_description: Finniss mine, which began production in Q1 2023, announced a temporary halt in mining operations on January 5, 2024.
events.description: Finniss mine, which began production in Q1 2023, announced a temporary halt in mining operations on January 5, 2024.

events.name: Greenbushes Mine
events.wd_description: Greenbushes mine has adjusted its FY2024 production guidance from 140-150k tons to 130-140k tons.
events.description: Greenbushes mine has adjusted its FY2024 production guidance from 140-150k tons to 130-140k tons.

events.name: Liontown Projects
events.wd_description: Liontown Resources is reviewing the expansion plans for the Kathleen Valley project, potentially delaying the second phase.
events.description: Liontown Resources is reviewing the expansion plans for the Kathleen Valley project, potentially delaying the second phase.

events.name: Other Australian Mines
events.wd_description: Other Australian lithium mines, such as Wodgina and Mt Cattlin, continue stable operations, while Pilgangoora and Mt Marion report significant production increases in Q4 2023.

events.name: South American Salt Lakes
events.wd_description: South American lithium projects, particularly in the lithium triangle, continue to leverage their cost advantages, with several new projects expected to commence production in the near future.

events.name: Atacama Project
events.wd_description: The Atacama project remains one of the key lithium production sites in South America, benefiting from significant cost advantages.

events.name: Olaroz Project
events.wd_description: The Olaroz project continues stable production with plans for expansion to meet future demand.

events.name: New Projects
events.wd_description: Several new projects, including the 3Q project by Zijin Mining and the Centenario project by Eramet, are expected to begin production in 2024, though overall production growth may slow.

events.name: African Lithium Mines
events.wd_description: African lithium projects are expanding rapidly, with significant developments in countries such as Zimbabwe, Mali, Ghana, and the DRC.

events.name: Bikita Project
events.wd_description: The Bikita project in Zimbabwe is one of the major lithium production sites in Africa, contributing significantly to the region's output.

events.name: Arcadia Project

events.name: New Projects

events.name: North American Lithium Projects
events.wd_description: North American lithium projects are making significant progress, with several in production and others in the development phase.

events.name: Tanco Project
events.wd_description: The Tanco project in Canada is a significant contributor to North America's lithium supply, with ongoing production.

events.name: NAL Project
events.wd_description: The NAL project in Canada continues stable production, adding to the region's lithium output.

events.name: New Projects
events.wd_description: New projects such as James Bay, Nemaska, and Carolina are expected to enhance North America's lithium production capacity significantly.

events.name: Australian Lithium Production Developments
events.wd_description: Various Australian lithium projects are experiencing production developments, including expansions, stable operations, and temporary shutdowns.

events.name: Finniss Project
events.wd_description: The Finniss lithium project, operated by Core Lithium, has temporarily halted mining operations while continuing to process existing ore stockpiles.
events.description: The Finniss lithium project, operated by Core Lithium, has temporarily halted mining operations while continuing to process existing ore stockpiles.

events.name: Ore Stockpiles
events.wd_description: The existing ore stockpiles at Finniss are sufficient to continue processing operations until mid-2024, without the need for further mining.
events.description: The existing ore stockpiles at Finniss are sufficient to continue processing operations until mid-2024, without the need for further mining.

events.name: Pilgangoora Project
events.wd_description: The Pilgangoora project, owned by Pilbara Minerals, continues to increase its production capacity with planned expansions to reach 1 million tons per year by 2025.
events.description: The Pilgangoora project, owned by Pilbara Minerals, continues to increase its production capacity with planned expansions to reach 1 million tons per year by 2025.

events.name: Expansion Plans
events.wd_description: Expansion projects P680 and P1000 at Pilgangoora are on track, with production capacity expected to reach 1 million tons per year by the first half of 2025.
events.description: Expansion projects P680 and P1000 at Pilgangoora are on track, with production capacity expected to reach 1 million tons per year by the first half of 2025.

events.name: Mt Cattlin Project
events.wd_description: The Mt Cattlin project, located in Western Australia, has seen significant production growth and resource updates, extending the mine's life.
events.description: The Mt Cattlin project, located in Western Australia, has seen significant production growth and resource updates, extending the mine's life.

events.name: Production Growth
events.wd_description: Production at Mt Cattlin increased significantly in Q3 2023, with FY2024 production guidance set at 210-230k tons.

events.name: Resource Updates
events.wd_description: The updated resource estimates have extended the mine life of Mt Cattlin, ensuring continued production.

events.name: Wodgina Project
events.wd_description: The Wodgina project is steadily increasing its production capacity, with plans to reach 1 million tons per year by 2025.

events.name: Production Capacity
events.wd_description: Wodgina's production capacity is set to reach 1 million tons per year by 2025, positioning it as one of the largest hard rock lithium mines globally.
